description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has risen on Trinity Ward at Mount Vernon Hospital for a fixed term (6 months secondment cover) Band 6 post, within our team on the elective orthopaedic inpatient unit and mixed speciality day care unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mount Vernon Hospital Treatment Centre is, due to its elective service, a Green Site in relation to the Covid-19 pandemic. We have a robust programme in place where patients are screened for Covid-19 and asked to isolate prior to admission, and staff are currently part of a 2 weekly screening programme themselves.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mount Vernon Hospital Treatment Centre is part of the Hillingdon Hospitals Trust and situated in rural Northwood on the outskirts of London and Hertfordshire. It is within easy access of the M25 and close to vital tube and bus links. The Metropolitan tube line is only a short bus or walk away.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trinity team cover both the 16 bedded elective inpatient area and the mixed speciality day care unit which are situated across the same floor. Trinity unit will be increasing the amount of elective orthopaedic surgery carried out daily as well as operating on higher numbers of patients with complex medical conditions. Our current senior nursing team consists of 1 ward manager and 5 Band 6 junior sisters / charge nurses. To help us continue to deliver a high standard of care to all patients on the unit we are looking to recruit a 6 month fixed term Band 6 to cover a secondment to our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced nurse, preferably with orthopaedic / surgical/acute care nursing backgrounds who have a passion for orthopaedic nursing.. You will be joining a team of dedicated nursing, medical and therapy staff. The right candidate must have strong communication skills and proven leadership qualities. The mentorship course is essential, as well as an interest in developing practise within the surgical unit. You must have at least three years experience as a registered nurse with a minimum of 12 months experience in either orthopaedics, surgery or acute medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to work alternating shifts involving long days and night duty. A full orientation will be given on induction to the ward. There is some opportunity for development as the Trust offers in house training in venepuncture and cannulation, ECG interpretation, ALERT, ILS and the deteriorating patient study day to name a few.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Debbie Field&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Ward manager Trinity unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: debbie.field2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01923 844 355&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I am available Mon - Friday until 3:30pm.&lt;/p&gt;
